{
  "texts": [
    "The reports generated were unguided, i.e., neither \"Expert Guidance\" nor \"Classifier Guidance\" was used.",
    "One pathologist at each institution analyzed the reports, ignoring differences in report format due to language or reporting standards.",
    "A second pathologist double-checked the results.",
    "They agreed to use the following scores to grade the reports (see Methods for details): (5) beyond expectation, (4) highly accurate, (3) generally accurate with minor variations without clinical impact, (2) partially accurate with variations that could have clinical impact, (1) minimally accurate, (0) completely inaccurate.",
    "A score greater than 2 indicates a diagnosis that is considered correct or within an acceptable range of subjectivity (Fig. 6b)."
  ]
}